    "id": "q-hssc-cet-m6-35",
    "text": "A can do a piece of work in 15 days and B can do the same work in 20 days. If they work together for 4 days, what fraction of the work is left? / A किसी कार्य को 15 दिनों में कर सकता है और B उसी कार्य को 20 दिनों में कर सकता है। यदि वे 4 दिनों तक एक साथ कार्य करते हैं, तो कार्य का कितना भाग शेष बचेगा?",
    "options": [
      "7/15 / 7/15",
      "8/15 / 8/15",
      "11/15 / 11/15",
      "2/5 / 2/5"
    ],
    "correctIndex": 1,
    "explanation": "Correct Answer: B\n\nDetailed Explanation & Step-by-step Solution:\nLet the total work be 1. (Alternatively, let total work be the LCM of 15 and 20, which is 60 units).\nWork done by A in 1 day = 1/15 of the total work\nWork done by B in 1 day = 1/20 of the total work\n\nWork done by both A and B together in 1 day:\n= 1/15 + 1/20\n= (4 + 3) / 60\n= 7/60 of the total work\n\nWork done by both in 4 days:\n= 4 × (7/60)\n= 7/15 of the total work\n\nRemaining work = 1 - (Work done in 4 days)\nRemaining work = 1 - 7/15 = 8/15.\n\nShortcut Method:\nTotal work = LCM(15, 20) = 60 units.\nEfficiency of A = 60 / 15 = 4 units/day.\nEfficiency of B = 60 / 20 = 3 units/day.\nCombined efficiency of A and B = 4 + 3 = 7 units/day.\nWork done in 4 days = 7 × 4 = 28 units.\nRemaining work = 60 - 28 = 32 units.\nFraction of work left = 32 / 60 = 8/15.\n\nCommon Mistakes:\nStudents might calculate the fraction of work completed (7/15) instead of the remaining work.\n\nExtra Learning Point:\nUsing LCM as the total work is highly efficient as it avoids working with fractions during intermediate steps.\n\nPYQ Connection:\nCommon pattern in HSSC CET Group C & D and SSC GD examinations.",
