    "text": "The difference between compound interest (compounded annually) and simple interest on a sum of money for 2 years at 8% per annum is ₹32. Find the sum. / 8% प्रति वर्ष की दर से 2 वर्षों के लिए किसी धनराशि पर चक्रवृद्धि ब्याज (वार्षिक रूप से संयोजित) और साधारण ब्याज के बीच का अंतर ₹32 है। वह धनराशि ज्ञात कीजिए।",
    "options": [
      "₹4,000 / ₹4,000",
      "₹4,500 / ₹4,500",
      "₹5,000 / ₹5,000",
      "₹6,000 / ₹6,000"
    ],
    "correctIndex": 2,
    "explanation": "Correct Answer: C\n\nDetailed Explanation & Step-by-step Solution:\nLet the Principal sum be P.\nRate of interest (R) = 8% per annum\nTime (T) = 2 years\n\nSimple Interest (SI) for 2 years = P × R × T / 100 = P × 8 × 2 / 100 = 16P / 100\nCompound Interest (CI) for 2 years = P × (1 + R/100)² - P\nCI = P × (1 + 8/100)² - P\nCI = P × (1.08)² - P\nCI = P × (1.1664 - 1) = 0.1664P = 16.64P / 100\n\nDifference (CI - SI) = 16.64P / 100 - 16P / 100 = 0.64P / 100\nGiven difference = ₹32\nSo, 0.64P / 100 = 32\n64P / 10,000 = 32\nP = (32 × 10,000) / 64\nP = 10,000 / 2 = ₹5,000.\n\nShortcut Method:\nFor 2 years, the difference between CI and SI is given by the formula:\nDifference (D) = P × (R / 100)²\n32 = P × (8 / 100)²\n32 = P × (64 / 10,000)\nP = (32 × 10,000) / 64 = ₹5,000.\n\nCommon Mistakes:\nApplying the 3-year difference formula instead of the 2-year difference formula.\n\nExtra Learning Point:\nFor 3 years, the difference formula is: D = P × (R / 100)² × (300 + R) / 100.\n\nPYQ Connection:\nThis difference-based problem is widely tested across all competitive exams in India including SSC and HSSC.",
