    "correctIndex": 0,
    "explanation": "Correct Answer: Option A (Maintenance)\n\nDetailed Explanation:\n- The correct spelling is 'Maintenance'. It refers to the process of preserving a condition or situation or the state of being maintained.\n- The other options ('Maintainance', 'Maintanance', 'Maintenence') are incorrect spellings.\n\nStep-by-step Solution:\n1. Analyze the root word: The verb is 'maintain' (m-a-i-n-t-a-i-n).\n2. Note the suffix change: When converting the verb 'maintain' into the noun form, the '-tain' changes to '-ten-' before adding '-ance'.\n3. Hence, it becomes M-a-i-n-t-e-n-a-n-c-e.\n4. Compare with the options: Option A is the correct spelling.\n\nShortcut Method:\nBreak the word down phonetically: Main-te-nance. Notice that the middle syllable is 'te' (not 'tai' as in maintain). Remembering the phonetic breakdown 'Main-te-nance' prevents spelling errors.\n\nCommon Mistakes:\nThe most common mistake is spelling it as 'Maintainance' by keeping the spelling of the verb 'maintain' intact and just adding '-ance'. Always remember that the vowel changes from 'ai' to 'e'.\n\nExtra Learning Point:\nSimilar words that undergo spelling changes from verb to noun:\n- Pronounce -> Pronunciation (not Pronouncian)\n- Explain -> Explanation (not Explaination)\n- Sustain -> Sustenance (not Sustainance)\n\nPYQ Connection:\nSpelling correction questions are a mandatory part of the English section in HSSC CET Group D. 'Maintenance' is one of the most frequently asked words in competitive exams due to its deceptive root spelling.",
