    "id": "q-hssc-cet-m4-37",
    "text": "In a row of children facing North, Aman is 7th from the left and Priya is 5th from the right. If there are 15 children in total in the row, how many children are there between Aman and Priya? / उत्तर की ओर मुख किए बच्चों की एक पंक्ति में, अमन बाएं से 7वें स्थान पर है और प्रिया दाएं से 5वें स्थान पर है। यदि पंक्ति में कुल 15 बच्चे हैं, तो अमन और प्रिया के बीच कितने बच्चे हैं?",
    "options": [
      "2",
      "3",
      "4",
      "1"
    ],
    "correctIndex": 1,
    "explanation": "Priya's position from the left = (Total + 1) − position from right = (15 + 1) − 5 = 11th from the left. Aman is 7th from the left and Priya is 11th from the left, so the children strictly between them occupy positions 8, 9, and 10 — a count of (11 − 7 − 1) = 3 children. Option A (2) results from forgetting to subtract 1 for an exclusive count; Option C (4) and D (1) result from miscounting the position boundaries. / प्रिया की बाएं से स्थिति = (कुल + 1) − दाएं से स्थिति = (15 + 1) − 5 = बाएं से 11वीं। अमन बाएं से 7वें स्थान पर है और प्रिया बाएं से 11वें स्थान पर है, इसलिए दोनों के बीच के बच्चों की संख्या (11 − 7 − 1) = 3 है।\n\n**Shortcut Method:** Number of people between two positions (both counted from the same side) = (larger position − smaller position − 1).\n**Exam Tip:** Always convert both positions to the same reference side (left or right) before calculating the gap between them — mixing sides is the most common error in seating-position questions.\n**Extra Learning Point:** The formula \"(Total + 1) − position from one side = position from the other side\" is the single most useful formula in linear seating arrangement questions.",
