    "correctIndex": 2,
    "explanation": "With 6 people around a circular table, P and S sit opposite each other, splitting the table into two sides of 2 seats each. Q is immediately right of P, and R sits between Q and S — meaning the order going right from P is P→Q→R→S. The remaining two friends, T and U, must fill the two seats on the other side (going left from P to S), but their exact order is not determinable from the given information, so the immediate left of P is either T or U. / 6 लोगों के साथ एक वृत्ताकार मेज़ पर, P और S एक-दूसरे के सामने बैठते हैं, जिससे मेज़ दो भागों में बंट जाती है, प्रत्येक में 2 सीटें। Q, P के ठीक दाईं ओर है, और R, Q और S के बीच बैठा है — अर्थात P से दाईं ओर जाने पर क्रम है P→Q→R→S। शेष दो मित्र, T और U, दूसरी तरफ की दो सीटों को भरते हैं, परंतु दिए गए विवरण से उनका सटीक क्रम निर्धारित नहीं किया जा सकता, इसलिए P के ठीक बाईं ओर T या U में से कोई एक है।\n\n**Shortcut Method:** In circular seating puzzles, always fix one person's position first, then build the arrangement step by step in one direction before checking the other side.\n**Exam Tip:** When information is insufficient to fully determine an arrangement, recognize that the answer may legitimately be \"cannot be determined\" or a pair of possibilities — don't force a single definite answer that isn't supported by the given clues.\n**Extra Learning Point:** This question deliberately demonstrates that not all seating-arrangement clues fully constrain every seat — a key skill for circular arrangement puzzles is recognizing when information is genuinely incomplete.",
