    "correctIndex": 1,
    "explanation": "Following BODMAS: first solve inside the brackets: 15×8=120, 120−24=96. Then divide: 96÷4=24. Then solve the power: 6²=36. Finally add: 24+36=60. Option A (54) results from a power mistake (6²=30 incorrectly); Option C (56) results from a division slip; Option D (64) results from squaring 8 instead of 6 somewhere in the steps. / BODMAS के अनुसार: पहले कोष्ठक के अंदर हल करें: 15×8=120, 120−24=96। फिर भाग करें: 96÷4=24। फिर घात हल करें: 6²=36। अंत में जोड़ें: 24+36=60।\n\n**Shortcut Method:** Always solve brackets first, then powers/roots, then division/multiplication (left to right), then addition/subtraction (left to right) — the standard BODMAS order.\n**Exam Tip:** A common trap is solving addition before completing the power calculation — always finish 6² fully before adding.\n**Extra Learning Point:** BODMAS stands for Brackets, Of, Division, Multiplication, Addition, Subtraction — some textbooks use PEMDAS (Parentheses, Exponents, Multiplication, Division, Addition, Subtraction), which follows the same logical order.",
