    "id": "q-hssc-cet-m4-44",
    "text": "A shopkeeper bought an item for ₹800 and sold it for ₹920. What was his profit percentage? / एक दुकानदार ने एक वस्तु ₹800 में खरीदी और ₹920 में बेची। उसका लाभ प्रतिशत कितना था?",
    "options": [
      "12%",
      "13%",
      "14%",
      "15%"
    ],
    "correctIndex": 3,
    "explanation": "Profit = Selling Price − Cost Price = 920 − 800 = ₹120. Profit% = (Profit/CP)×100 = (120/800)×100 = 15%. Options A, B, and C result from using the wrong base (selling price instead of cost price) or rounding errors. / लाभ = विक्रय मूल्य − क्रय मूल्य = 920 − 800 = ₹120। लाभ% = (लाभ/क्रय मूल्य)×100 = (120/800)×100 = 15%।\n\n**Shortcut Method:** Profit/Loss percentage is always calculated on the Cost Price (CP), never on the Selling Price (SP) — this is the single most important rule to remember.\n**Exam Tip:** A frequent trap is calculating percentage using SP as the denominator instead of CP — always double-check which value is the base.\n**Extra Learning Point:** If a question asks for profit/loss percentage \"on selling price\" specifically (a less common variant), the denominator changes to SP — always read the question wording carefully.",
