    "text": "A train travels at a speed of 60 km/h for 2.5 hours. What distance does it cover? / एक रेलगाड़ी 60 किमी/घंटा की गति से 2.5 घंटे तक यात्रा करती है। वह कितनी दूरी तय करती है?",
    "options": [
      "120 km",
      "130 km",
      "150 km",
      "140 km"
    ],
    "correctIndex": 2,
    "explanation": "Distance = Speed × Time = 60 km/h × 2.5 h = 150 km. Options A, B, and C result from rounding or multiplication errors using an incorrect time value. / दूरी = गति × समय = 60 किमी/घंटा × 2.5 घंटा = 150 किमी।\n\n**Shortcut Method:** Memorize the core formula triangle: Distance = Speed × Time; Speed = Distance/Time; Time = Distance/Speed — rearrange as needed based on what's asked.\n**Exam Tip:** Always check the units given in the question (km/h, m/s) match the units required in the answer — unit conversion errors are a very common trap (1 m/s = 18/5 km/h).\n**Extra Learning Point:** For relative speed problems (trains crossing each other, boats in streams), the same Distance=Speed×Time formula is applied after first calculating the combined or relative speed.",
